$ %ProgramData%\Microsoft\VisualStudio\Packages

This is the default directory where → Windows/development/Visual-Studio stores package manifests and (optionally) payloads.
Non-default locations are stored in the `CachePath` value below the first → Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[registry key] that is found in the following list:
    • `HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\VisualStudio\Setup`]
    • `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/VisualStudio/Setup[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\VisualStudio]\Setup`]
    • `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Wow6432Node/Microsoft/VisualStudio[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\WOW6432Node\Microsoft\VisualStudio]\Setup`

Apparently, this directory is also referred to as the *Download cache*.

links:
  → https://devblogs.microsoft.com/setup/moving-or-disabling-the-package-cache-for-visual-studio-2017/
